# INFO

This projects is for fast backup of linux servers on the network via SSH & SCP

The server that will run these script will have to configure key authentication on the client system (with user root)

The Backup-By-Ssh.sh gets it parameter from command line and then go through its configuration to backup the servers
specific settings can be configured to each server as a script that will be located in the scripts dir.

It goes something like this

the Backup-By-Ssh.sh compile a script that will run on the client host via the header and footer files & a specific script from the scripts dir.
then the script get copied via scp to the client host and executed.
after this there will be a tbz file in the /tmp of the client and it will be copied to the specified location.

Please use with caution and go through the script before implementing it...

